oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Arthur Mathews at Crossville Fire Department
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of Arthur Mathews (on left) and an unidentified man standing next to a fire truck inside the Crossville Fire Department. Mathews was Fire Chief and Chief of Police at the time. Note: this negative was cut in half.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Men; Fire fighters; Fire engines; Police; Fire stations
